lic_at":"2020-06-11T19:35:58.766Z","comments_closed?":true,"facebook_team?":false,"team_private?":false,"vulnerability_information":"**Target Url**\n████/services/user/closeAccount\n\n**Summary:**\nHello, I found a Cross Site Request Forgery bug in the target endpoint on the POST request `/█████/services/user/closeAccount` which is critical because it can delete authenticated user account whenever he navigates to the attacker website or link.\n\n## Step-by-step Reproduction Instructions\n\n1. Navigate to your account █████████/#/login.\n2. Copy and paste the below code in an html file\n ```\n\u003chtml\u003e\n  \u003c!-- CSRF PoC - generated by Burp Suite Professional --\u003e\n  \u003cbody\u003e\n  \u003cscript\u003ehistory.pushState('', '', '/')\u003c/script\u003e\n    \u003cform action=\"████████/services/user/closeAccount\" method=\"POST\"\u003e\n      \u003cinput type=\"submit\" value=\"Submit request\" /\u003e\n    \u003c/form\u003e\n  \u003c/body\u003e\n\u003c/html\u003e```\n\nOpen it in the browser, hit the button and your account will be closed.\n\nPlease see the attached video for a clear poc.\n████████\n\n## Suggested Mitigation/Remediation Actions\nAdd a csrf-token in the header or in an hidden input to check if the user that is doing this action authorized or not.\n\n## Impact\n\nThis action is critical and sensitive. Attacker can upload this file to a url. Sends it to the victims. And when the authenticated victims navigate to the url their accounts will be deleted.","weakness":{"id":45,"name":"Cross-Site Request Forgery (CSRF)"},"original_report_id":null,"original_report_url":null,"attachments":[],"allow_singular_disclosure_at":null,"vote_count":20,"voters":["bhovington","mohamed-magdi","renniepak","brahim_boufakri01","realtess","0nlymohammed","updatelap","taha_halabi","dastan_9408","sa1tama0","and 10 more..."],"severity":{"rating":"medium","author_type":"Team"},"structured_scope":null,"abilities":{"assignable_team_members":[],"assignable_team_member_